Good question üëç
You are asking about **ONE-DIRECTION vs TWO-DIRECTION data flow** in the context of
üëâ ViewBag, ViewData, TempData (ASP.NET MVC)

---

# ‚úÖ Important Truth (from scratch)

In ASP.NET MVC:

### ‚úî ViewBag

### ‚úî ViewData

### ‚úî TempData

All three are **ONE-DIRECTION ONLY**

### That direction is:

```
Controller  ‚ûú  View
```

You CANNOT send data back from View to Controller using them.

So:

| Feature  | Direction |
| -------- | --------- |
| ViewBag  | ‚ûú One way |
| ViewData | ‚ûú One way |
| TempData | ‚ûú One way |

---

# üîÑ 2-DIRECTION (Two-way) Data Flow happens with MODEL

Two-direction communication happens when using:
‚úÖ Strongly Typed Model
‚úÖ Form Submission (POST)

Example:

```
Controller ‚Üí View ‚Üí User modifies ‚Üí View ‚Üí Controller
```

That is TWO-direction.

---

# ‚úÖ Simple Comparison

## ONE DIRECTION (Display only)

```csharp
ViewBag.Name = "Onkar";
```

Flow:

```
Controller ‚Üí View (Display)
```

---

## TWO DIRECTION (Editable + Return)

```csharp
public IActionResult Edit()
{
    return View(studentModel);
}

[HttpPost]
public IActionResult Edit(Student model)
{
    // data comes back from View ‚úÖ
}
```

Flow:

```
Controller ‚Üí View ‚Üí Controller
```

This is two-direction using Model Binding.

---

# üî• Clear Cheat Sheet

| Mechanism     | Direction | Can View send back? |
| ------------- | --------- | ------------------- |
| ViewBag       | One-way   | ‚ùå No                |
| ViewData      | One-way   | ‚ùå No                |
| TempData      | One-way   | ‚ùå No                |
| Model Binding | Two-way   | ‚úÖ Yes               |

---

# ‚úÖ Real-Life Analogy

* ViewBag/ViewData = Teacher writes on board (students read only)
* Model Binding = Student answers back to teacher ‚úÖ

---

# ‚úÖ Interview-ready Line

> ViewBag, ViewData and TempData provide one-way communication from Controller to View, whereas Model Binding allows two-way communication between View and Controller.

